'''Harold Edwin Stafford''' ([[20 April]] [[1921]] - [[18 January]] [[2005]]) was a [[Liberal Party of Canada|Liberal party]] member of the [[Canadian House of Commons]]. He was born in [[Fredericton]], [[New Brunswick]] and became a lawyer by career.

After two defeats at the [[Elgin (electoral district)|Elgin]] riding in the [[Canadian federal election, 1962|1962]] and [[Canadian federal election, 1963|1963 federal elections]], Stafford was elected there in the [[Canadian federal election, 1965|1965 election]] and re-elected in [[Canadian federal election, 1968|1968]]. After serving two terms, the [[27th Canadian Parliament|27th]] and [[28th Canadian Parliament]]s, Stafford was defeated in the [[Canadian federal election, 1972|1972 election]] by [[John Wise (politician)|John Wise]] of the [[Progressive Conservative Party of Canada|Progressive Conservative party]].
